## Stop an agent

Instruct an agent to stop accepting new build jobs and shut itself down.

```bash
curl -X PUT "https://api.buildkite.com/v2/organizations/{org.slug}/agents/{id}/stop" \
  -d '{
    "force": true
  }'
```

Optional [request body properties](/docs/api#request-body-properties):

<table>
<tbody>
  <tr><th><code>force</code></th><td>If the agent is currently processing a job, the job and the build will be cancelled.<p class="Docs__api-param-eg"><em>Default:</em> <code>true</code></p></td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

Required scope: `write_agents`

Success response: `204 No Content`

Error responses:

<table>
<tbody>
  <tr><th><code>400 Bad Request</code></th><td><code>{ "message": "Can only stop connected agents" }</code></td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
